    "summary": "Ton Meershoek joined the Netherlands Authority for the Financial markets (AFM) in April 2005 becoming Technical Expert financial Reporting in April 2013. Before he had the positions of head Financial Reporting Supervision Division (2008 - 2013), he was manager and senior supervisor. The Financial Reporting Supervision Division  division is responsible for the supervision of the financial reporting of listed companies. \n\nTon has been the AFM-representative in European advisory bodies and committees, such as the ESMA-CRSC (European Securities and Markets Authority - Corporate Reporting Standing Committee). As of August 2016, he chairs the EECS meetings (European Enforcement Coordination Sessions, of which he is member since 2007) Between March 2011 and August 2016 Ton chaired the ESMA working group on IFRS, a permanent taskforce. Since 2018 Ton is member of the Narrative Reporting Working Group of ESMA\u2019s CRSC. This permanent task force acts in the field of Non-Financial Information (NFI) and Alternative Performance Measures (APMs) As of November 2011, Meershoek represents the AFM in Committee 1 of International Organization of Securities Commissions (IOSCO). Ton has been the IOSCO C1 observer on the IFRS IC and the IOSCO C1 member on the IFRS Advisory Council. \n\nBesides his work for the AFM Ton has been a lecturer on financial reporting since 1992 at the Nyenrode Business University. Ton was lecturer of the year 2013/14 in the Post Master Phase.\n\nPrior to working for the AFM Meershoek has spent several years as an internal revenue agent at the Dutch Tax Authorities, as a controller and accounting manager in AkzoNobel and as a group controller and CFO of the Dutch Corporate Identity firm Total Identity.\n\nMeershoek is a certified auditor and a certified Management Accountant. He studied accounting and auditing at the Nederlands Instituut van Registeraccountants (NIvRA) and finalized the Postgraduate study at the Vrije Universiteit of Amsterdam",
